Setting Up Apple Volume Purchasing Program (VPP)
2015-12-17 23:28
Apps/eBooks Distribution and Management
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea"><br></div>Cellabus installs apps using Apple’s VPP Managed Distribution, which offers flexibility with managing apps and recycling licenses as against VPP redemption codes. More details about the managed distribution can be found in the VPP Program Guide for Education&nbsp;<span class="s2"><a href="http://images.apple.com/education/docs/VPP_Education_Guide_EN_Feb14.pdf">http://images.apple.com/education/docs/VPP_Education_Guide_EN_Feb14.pdf</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><br><span style="line-height: 1.4em;"><br>If your school has already bought VPP redemption codes for apps before, codes that are still unredeemed or were previously redeemed through Apple Configurator; those codes can easily be migrated to licenses which can then be managed using Cellabus. More information about the migration can be found here </span><span class="s2"><a href="http://support.apple.com/kb/HT6015">http://support.apple.com/kb/HT6015</a><br></span><span style="line-height: 1.4em;"><br>In order to use any of Cellabus' Application Management features, you need to enter your VPP information into Cellabus.&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.4em;">If and once you have a VPP account, <b>enter your VPP Service Token</b>. To do this:</span><h3 class="p1"><br>Obtain the Service Token file from your Apple VPP Account:</h3><br>1. Sign into your Apple VPP account at&nbsp;https://volume.itunes.apple.com/store <br><br>2. Choose Account Summary&nbsp;under your email on the top right<br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="https://cellabus.uservoice.com/assets/80610984/vppaccount.jpg"><br><br>3. Download the token from the Account Summary page, by clicking the&nbsp;Download Token&nbsp;button as below.<br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="https://cellabus.uservoice.com/assets/80611080/vpptoken.png"><br><br><br><br><b>Enter VPP Service Token into Cellabus</b><div class="layoutArea"><br><br></div><div class="layoutArea"><span style="line-height: 1.4em;">1. Open the downloaded token in text editor like Notepad or TextEdit.<br><br>2. Select and copy the entire content of the file<br><br><span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img src="https://cellabus.uservoice.com/assets/80611575/stoken.png"></span><br><br><br>3. Go the&nbsp;<b>﻿Settings Page&nbsp;</b>﻿on your Cellabus Dashboard from the menu bar or directly at https://yourschool.cellabus.com<br><br>4. Paste the content of the token file into the text are labeled&nbsp;<b>﻿VPP Token&nbsp;</b>﻿and then click&nbsp;<b>﻿Update<br></b><b><br><span><img src="https://cellabus.uservoice.com/assets/80611734/settings.png"></span><br></b><br>5. Cellabus automatically syncs information &nbsp;with Apple's Servers. In order to do immediately, go the <b>Homepage</b>, and click "Refresh VPP Data From Apple."<br></span><span style="line-height: 1.4em;"><br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><p class="p1"></p><p class="p1"></p>
<br>
